Class Cache<K,V>

    • io.github.juanmuscaria.jmutils.utils.Cache<K,V>

  • public class Cache<K,V>

    A minimal thread-safe time-based cache implementation backed by a HashMap and TreeMultimap.

      • Cache

        public Cache(long retention,
             Function<V> inUseCheck,
             Function<V> postRemoval)
        Constructs a Cache with the specified retention duration, in use function, and post-removal function.
        Parameters:
        retention - duration after which keys are automatically invalidated if not in use
        inUseCheck - Function used to check if a key is considered in use
        postRemoval - Function used to perform any operations required when a key is invalidated

    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put(K key,
                V value)
        Set a key and value pair. Keys are unique. Using an existing key will cause the old value to be overwritten and the expiration timer to be reset.
        Parameters:
        key - key with which the specified value is to be associated
        value - value to be associated with the specified key
